  </p>
  <p>
Now, I don’t know the specifics of what causes someone to vote for either Jill Stein or Gary Johnson myself, but I am going to take a wild stab in the dark and guess that most people in those camps would have, gun to their head, preferred Clinton over Trump.  4 out of 5 Gary Johnson supporters are probably disgruntled Bernie fans who were razzed to hear that Gary supports weed legalization.  The other 1 out of 5 are actual Libertarians.  5 out of 5 Jill Stein supporters are probably-vegan liberals trying to be edgy who would never dare vote Trump otherwise.  I just made these statistics up, but it’s probably not too much worse than how the polls this election cycle have fared.
